Design Decisions to Know Cold (Interview)
1. "Why AST chunking instead of fixed-line?"
Fixed-line can cut a function in half → the embedding represents a fragment, not a complete idea → retrieval quality drops. AST chunking guarantees every chunk is a complete function or class.

2. "Why keep classes as single chunks instead of splitting methods?"
If you split methods out, each method chunk loses the class docstring, class-level attributes, and the relationship between methods. For search, "class Calculator with add and multiply" as one chunk is more useful than three orphaned method chunks.

3. "Why deterministic chunk IDs?"
Re-indexing the same repo produces the same IDs → ChromaDB can upsert without creating duplicates. UUIDs would create duplicates every time.

4. "Why to_search_text() includes metadata?"
Without it, searching for a function by name would only match if that name appeared in the code body. Prepending "function parse_file in code_parser.py:" makes names and file paths directly searchable by both BM25 and embeddings.

5. "What about files with no functions?"
The module fallback catches config files, init files, and small scripts (≤ 200 lines). Without it, those files are invisible to search — a real gap in coverage.

